<div id="review_1720731904" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1720731904" />
    <a title="Christine Cimo" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10718879-christine-cimo"><img alt="Christine Cimo" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1470630595p2/10718879.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1720731904?book_show_action=true">Aug 06, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Christine Cimo" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Christine Cimo" href="/user/show/10718879-christine-cimo">Christine Cimo</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1720731904" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18178346418682137181">“The Sailweaver’s Son,” by Jeff Minerd proves to be a captivating, lucid and well-crafted art of fiction. “The Sailweaver’s Son,” offers a vivid and unique fantasy world where friendship, hardship, reality, and humor blend deeply and intricately – melding into a compelling narrative that one finds hard to ‘put down.’<br/><br/>The story follows the journey of a young teenaged boy named Taktinius (Tak). Similar to most teens, Tak grapples to understand who he really is, what is his purpose, what are his str</span>
  <span id="freeText18178346418682137181" style="display:none">“The Sailweaver’s Son,” by Jeff Minerd proves to be a captivating, lucid and well-crafted art of fiction. “The Sailweaver’s Son,” offers a vivid and unique fantasy world where friendship, hardship, reality, and humor blend deeply and intricately – melding into a compelling narrative that one finds hard to ‘put down.’<br /><br />The story follows the journey of a young teenaged boy named Taktinius (Tak). Similar to most teens, Tak grapples to understand who he really is, what is his purpose, what are his strengths, and his weaknesses and how each facet of his character affects and intermingles within his world. Tak unveils his genuine nature by encapsulating bravery, truth, fear, mischief, and camaraderie. Throughout his extraordinary journey, Tak unearths what it truly means to go ‘above and beyond’ and inadvertently demonstrates the attributes of courage and selflessness. Tak learns to confront his fears and his mistakes head-on and illustrates how to think ‘outside of the box.’ <br /><br />“The Sailweaver’s Son,” is an enjoyable read for both teenagers and adults alike. It offers resonant character building and a fantastic world filled with rarity, beauty, and adventure. Minerd’s style of writing strikes a unique balance of intellect and understandability, capable of enchanting readers of all levels. I thoroughly enjoyed reading, “The Sailweaver’s Son,” and highly recommend this book to others as I eagerly wait for book 2!<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="18178346418682137181" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


